  "text": "The proper motion can be measured accurately by Gaia with uncertainties similar to the position on the sky, but the conversion to physical velocity involves the distance of the star and thus that source of uncertainty also plays an important role. For radial velocities, we assume an uncertainty of 5 km/s, although we expect many stars to be measured more accurately [CITATION_1] by surveys such as VLT [CITATION_2] 34] , WEAVE [CITATION_3] , and 4MOST [CITATION_4] . In our simulations, velocity uncertainties play a sub-dominant role compared to position uncertainties.",
